#Depression sucks.  Not just for the depressed person, but also for the family, friends, and supporters of the depressed person.  This article is for them.

Kudos to my wife for her courage to write this piece.  And all thanks to her for sticking with me during my darkest hours!

media.altText:
Depression as an identity
Has depression started to become comfortable? Is being depressed part of your identity?
Sometimes we can become stuck and feel numb to depression, and it may start to feel like a comfort zone. It can become hard to see out of it as it ends up being a safe and familiar place and all that you know.
You may even feel like you don’t want to get your hopes up about being happy, because you may feel like you have been let down before.
If any of this sounds familiar to you, know that you are not alone and that you can change your life!  No matter what challenges you are facing! The first step is reaching out and asking for help - the right person will never turn you away. Don’t give up if you have been turned away before and that wasn’t the right person to support you on your journey.
Read this helpful article on depression, and look out for some great resources at the end. https://purposefullife.com.au/insights/depression/
